obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5546)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5546&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Clinical`
  line `Establishments (Registration and Regulation) Act, 2010.`
  line
  line `(2) It applies, in the first instance, to the whole of the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Himachal Pradesh,`
  line `Mizoram and Sikkim and the Union territories; and it shall apply to such other State which adopts this`
  line `Act by resolution passed in that behalf under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Himachal Pradesh, Mizoram`
  line `and Sikkim and the Union territories, on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `appoint and in any other State which adopts this Act under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution, on`
  line `the date of such adoption; and any reference in this Act to the commencement of this Act shall, in relation`
  line `to any State or Union territory, mean the date on which this Act comes into force in such State or Union`
  line `territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different categories of clinical establishments and`
  line `for different recognised systems of medicine.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st March, 2012, vide notification No. S.O. 342(E), dated 28th February, 2012, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5547)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5547&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "authority" means the district registering authority set-up under section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) "certificate" means certificate of registration issued under section 30;`
  line
  line `(c) "clinical establishment" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a hospital, maternity home, nursing home, dispensary, clinic, sanatorium or an institution`
  line `by whatever name called that offers services, facilities requiring diagnosis, treatment or care for`
  line `illness, injury, deformity, abnormality or pregnancy in any recognised system of medicine`
  line `established and administered or maintained by any person or body of persons, whether`
  line `incorporated or not; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a place established as an independent entity or part of an establishment referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (i), in connection with the diagnosis or treatment of diseases where pathological,`
  line `bacteriological, genetic, radiological, chemical, biological investigations or other diagnostic or`
  line `investigative services with the aid of laboratory or other medical equipment, are usually carried`
  line `on, established and administered or maintained by any person or body of persons, whether`
  line `incorporated or not,`
  line
  line `and shall include a clinical establishment owned, controlled or managed by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Government or a department of the Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a trust, whether public or private;`
  line
  line `(c) a corporation (including a society) registered under a Central, Provincial or State Act, whether`
  line `or not owned by the Government;`
  line
  line `(d) a local authority; and`
  line
  line `(e) a single doctor,`
  line
  line `but does not include the clinical establishments owned, controlled or managed by the Armed Forces.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause "Armed Forces" means the forces constituted under the`
  line `Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950) , the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950) and the Navy Act, 1957`
  line `(62 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(d) "emergency medical condition" means a medical condition manifesting itself by acute`
  line `symptoms of sufficient severity (including severe pain) of such a nature that the absence of immediate`
  line `medical attention could reasonably be expected to result in--`
  line
  line `(i) placing the health of the individual or, with respect to a pregnant women, the health of the`
  line `woman or her unborn child, in serious jeopardy; or`
  line
  line `(ii) serious impairment to bodily functions; or`
  line
  line `(iii) serious dysfunction of any organ or part of a body;`
  line
  line `(e) "National Council" means the National Council for clinical establishments established under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act by the Central Government or, as`
  line `the case may be, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(h) "recognised system of medicine" means Allopathy, Yoga, Naturopathy, Ayurveda,`
  line `Homoeopathy, Siddha and Unani System of medicines or any other system of medicine as may be`
  line `recognised by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) "register" means the register maintained by the authority, State Government and the Central`
  line `Government under sections 37, 38 and 39 respectively of this Act containing the number of clinical`
  line `establishments registered;`
  line
  line `(j) "registration" means to register under section 11 and the expression registration or registered`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(k) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "standards" means the conditions that the Central Government may prescribe under section`
  line `12, for the registration of clinical establishments;`
  line
  line `(n) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof`
  line `appointed under article 239 of the Constitution; and`
  line
  line `(o) "to stabilise (with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions)" means, with respect to`
  line `an emergency medical condition specified in clause (d), to provide such medical treatment of the`
  line `condition as may be necessary to assure, within reasonable medical probability, that no material`
  line `deterioration of the condition is likely to result from or occur during the transfer of the individual`
  line `from a clinical establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5548)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of National Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5548&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for the purposes of this Act, a`
  line `Council to be called the National Council for clinical establishments.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Council shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) Director-General of Health Service, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, ex officio, who`
  line `shall be the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) four representatives out of which one each to be elected by the--`
  line
  line `(i) Dental Council of India constituted under section 3 of the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(ii) Medical Council of India constituted under section 3 of the Indian Medical Council Act,`
  line `1956 (102 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(iii) Nursing Council of India constituted under section 3 of the Indian Nursing Council Act,`
  line `1947 (48 of 1947);`
  line
  line `(iv) Pharmacy Council of India constituted under section 3 of the Pharmacy Act, 1948`
  line `(8 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(c) three representatives to be elected by the Central Council of Indian Medicine representing the`
  line `Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani systems of medicine constituted under section 3 of the Indian Medicine`
  line `Central Council Act, 1970 (48 of 1970);`
  line
  line `(d) one representative to be elected by the Central Council of Homoeopathy constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Homoeopathy Central Council Act, 1973 (59 of 1973);`
  line
  line `(e) one representative to be elected by the Central Council of the Indian Medical Association;`
  line
  line `(f) one representative of Bureau of the Indian Sandards constituted under section 3 of the Bureau`
  line `of Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(g) two representatives from the Zonal Council set-up under section 15 of the States`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(h) two representatives from the North-Eastern Council set-up under section 3 of the`
  line `North-Eastern Council Act, 1971 (84 of 1971);`
  line
  line `(i) one representative from the line of paramedical systems excluding systems that have been`
  line `given representation under clause (b);`
  line
  line `(j) two representatives from National Level Consumer Group to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(k) one representative from the Associations of Indian Systems of Medicines relating to`
  line `Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(l) the Secretary-General of the Quality Council of India, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The nominated members of the National Council shall hold office for three years but shall be`
  line `eligible for re-nomination for maximum of one more term of three years.`
  line
  line `(4) The elected members of the National Council shall hold office for three years, but shall be eligible`
  line `for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person nominated or elected, as the case may be, shall hold office for such period`
  line `till he holds appointment of the office by virtue of which he was nominated or elected to the council.`
  line
  line `(5) The members of the National Council shall be entitled for such allowances as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The National Council may, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, make`
  line `bye-laws fixing a quorum and regulating its own procedure and the conduct of all business to be`
  line `transacted by it.`
  line
  line `(7) The National Council shall meet at least once in three months.`
  line
  line `(8) The National Council may constitute sub-committees and may appoint to such sub-committee, as`
  line `it deems fit, persons, who are not members of the National Council, for such period, not exceeding two`
  line `years, for the consideration of particular matters.`
  line
  line `(9) The functions of the National Council may be exercised notwithstanding any vacancy therein.`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Government shall appoint such person to be the Secretary of the National Council as`
  line `the Central Government may prescribe, and may provide the National Council with such other secretarial`
  line `and other staff as the Central Government considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5549)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Disqualifications for appointment as member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5549&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being`
  line `appointed as a member of the National Council if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(d) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a Corporation owned or`
  line `controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, such financial or other interest in the Council as`
  line `is likely to affect prejudicially the discharge by him of his functions as a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5550)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of National Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5550&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The National Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) compile and publish a National Register of clinical establishments within two years from the`
  line `date of the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) classify the clinical establishments into different categories;`
  line
  line `(c) develop the minimum standards and their periodic review;`
  line
  line `(d) determine within a period of two years from its establishment, the first set of standards for`
  line `ensuring proper healthcare by the clinical establishments;`
  line
  line `(e) collect the statistics in respect of clinical establishments;`
  line
  line `(f) perform any other function determined by the Central Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5551)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to seek advice or assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5551&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The National Council may associate with itself any person`
  line `or body whose assistance or advice it may desire in carrying out any of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5552)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `National Council to follow consultative process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5552&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The National Council shall follow a`
  line `consultative process for determining the standards and for classification of clinical establishments in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5553)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `State Council of clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5553&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall by notification`
  line `constitute a State Council for clinical establishments or the Union territory Council for clinical`
  line `establishments, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Council or the Union territory Council, as the case may be, shall consist of the`
  line `following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary, Health--ex officio, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) Director of Health Services--ex officio member-secretary;`
  line
  line `(c) Directors of different streams of Indian Systems of Medicine--ex officio members;`
  line
  line `(d) one representative each to be elected by the executive committee of--`
  line
  line `(i) State Medical Council of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) State Dental Council of India;`
  line
  line `(iii) State Nursing Council of India;`
  line
  line `(iv) State Pharmacy Council of India;`
  line
  line `(e) three representatives to be elected by the Executive of the State Council or the Union territory`
  line `Council, as the case may be, of Indian Medicine representing the Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani`
  line `systems of medicine;`
  line
  line `(f) one representative to be elected by the State Council of the Indian Medical Association;`
  line
  line `(g) one representative from the line of paramedical systems;`
  line
  line `(h) two representatives from State level consumer groups or reputed non-Governmental`
  line `organisations working in the field of health.`
  line
  line `(3) The nominated member of the State Council or the Union territory Council, as the case may be,`
  line `shall hold office for a term of three years, but shall be eligible for re-nomination for maximum of one`
  line `more term of three years.`
  line
  line `(4) The elected members of the State Council or the Union territory Council, as the case may be, shall`
  line `hold office for three years, but shall be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person nominated or elected, as the case may be, shall hold office for so long as he`
  line `holds the appointment of the office by virtue of which he was nominated or elected to the State Council or`
  line `the Union territory Council, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Council or the Union territory Council shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) compiling and updating the State Registers of clinical establishment;`
  line
  line `(b) sending monthly returns for updating the National Register;`
  line
  line `(c) representing the State in the National Council;`
  line
  line `(d) hearing of appeals against the orders of the authority; and`
  line
  line `(e) publication on annual basis a report on the state of implementation of standards within their`
  line `respective States.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5554)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Providing information to National Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5554&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the responsibility of the State Council`
  line `for clinical establishments to compile and update the State Register of clinical establishments of the State`
  line `and further to send monthly returns in digital format for updating the National Register.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5555)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authority for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5555&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification, set-up an authority`
  line `to be called the district registering authority for each district for registration of clinical establishments,`
  line `with the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) District Collector-- Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) District Health Officer--Convenor;`
  line
  line `(c) three members with such qualifications and on such terms and conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), for the purposes of provisional registration`
  line `of clinical establishments under section 14, the District Health Officer or the Chief Medical Officer (by`
  line `whatever name called) shall exercise the powers of the authority as per procedure that may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5556)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Registration for clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5556&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No person shall run a clinical establishment unless it`
  line `has been duly registered in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5557)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Condition for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5557&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) For registration and continuation, every clinical establishment`
  line `shall fulfil the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum standards of facilities and services as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) the minimum requirement of personnel as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(iii) provisions for maintenance of records and reporting as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(iv) such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The clinical establishment shall undertake to provide within the staff and facilities available, such`
  line `medical examination and treatment as may be required to stabilise the emergency medical condition of`
  line `any individual who comes or is brought to such clinical establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5558)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Classification of clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5558&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Clinical establishment of different systems shall`
  line `be classified into such categories, as may be prescribed by the Central Government, from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Different standards may be prescribed for classification of different categories referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that in prescribing the standards for clinical establishments, the Central Government shall`
  line `have regard to the local conditions.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5559)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Application for provisional certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5559&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of registration of`
  line `the clinical establishment under section 10, an application in the prescribed proforma along with the`
  line `prescribed fee shall be made to the authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The application shall be filed in person or by post or online.`
  line
  line `(3) The application shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by such details as may be`
  line `prescribed under this Act or rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) If any clinical establishment is in existence at the time of the commencement of this Act, an`
  line `application for its registration shall be made within one year from the date of the commencement of this`
  line `Act and a clinical establishment which comes into existence after commencement of this Act, shall apply`
  line `for permanent registration within a period of six months from the date of its establishment.`
  line
  line `(5) If any clinical establishment is already registered under any existing law requiring registration of`
  line `such establishments, even then it shall apply for registration as referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5560)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Provisional certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5560&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The authority shall, within a period of ten days from the date of receipt`
  line `of such application, grant to the applicant a certificate of provisional registration in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars and such information, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5561)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `No inquiry prior to provisional registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5561&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authority shall not conduct any inquiry`
  line `prior to the grant of provisional registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the grant of the provisional certificate of registration, the authority shall, within a`
  line `period of forty-five days from the grant of provisional registration, cause to be published in such manner,`
  line `as may be prescribed, all particulars of the clinical establishment so registered provisionally.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5562)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Validity of provisional registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5562&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 23, every provisional`
  line `registration shall be valid to the last day of the twelfth month from the date of issue of the certificate of`
  line `registration and such registration shall be renewable.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5563)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Display of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5563&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The certificate shall be kept affixed in a conspicuous`
  line `place in the clinical establishment in such manner so as to be visible to every one visiting such`
  line establishment.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5564)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Duplicate certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5564&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `In case the certificate is lost, destroyed, mutilated or damaged, the`
  line `authority shall issue a duplicate certificate on the request of the clinical establishment and on the payment`
  line `of such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5565)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Certificate to be non-transferable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5565&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The certificate of registration shall be non-transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of change of ownership or management, the clinical establishment shall inform the`
  line `authority of such change in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of change of category, or location, or on ceasing to function as a clinical`
  line `establishment, the certificate of registration in respect of such clinical establishment shall be surrendered`
  line `to the authority and the clinical establishment shall apply afresh for grant of certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5566)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Publication of expiry of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5566&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The authority shall cause to be published within such`
  line `time and in such manner, as may be prescribed, the names of clinical establishments whose registration`
  line `has expired.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5567)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Renewal of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5567&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The application for renewal of registration shall be made thirty days`
  line `before the expiry of the validity of the certificate of provisional registration and, in case the application for renewal is made after the expiry of the provisional registration, the authority shall allow renewal of`
  line `registration on payment of such enhanced fees, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5568)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Time limit for provisional registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5568&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the clinical establishments in respect of which`
  line `standards have been notified by the Central Government, provisional registration shall not be granted or`
  line `renewed beyond,--`
  line
  line `(i) the period of two years from the date of notification of the standards in case of clinical`
  line `establishments which came into existence before the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the period of two years from the date of notification of the standards for clinical`
  line `establishments which come into existence after the commencement of this Act but before the`
  line `notification of the standards; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the period of six months from the date of notification of standards for clinical establishments`
  line `which come into existence after standards have been notified.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5569)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Application for permanent registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5569&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Application for permanent registration by a clinical`
  line `establishment shall be made to the authority in such form and be accompanied by such fees, as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5570)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Verification of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5570&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The clinical establishment shall submit evidence of having`
  line `complied with the prescribed minimum standards in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5571)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Display of information for filing objections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5571&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `As soon as the clincial establishment submits the`
  line `required evidence of having complied with the prescribed minimum standards, the authority shall cause to`
  line `be displayed for information of the public at large and for filing objections, if any, in such manner, as may`
  line `be prescribed, all evidence submitted by the clinical establishment of having complied with the prescribed`
  line `minimum standards for a period of thirty days before processing for grant of permanent registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5572)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Communication of objections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5572&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If objections are received within the period referred to in the`
  line `preceding section, such objections shall be communicated to the clinical establishment for response`
  line `within a period of forty-five days.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5573)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Standards for permanent registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5573&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Permanent registration shall be granted only when a`
  line `clinical establishment fulfils the prescribed standards for registration by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5574)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Allowing or disallowing of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5574&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The authority shall pass an order immediately after`
  line `the expiry of the prescribed period and within the next thirty days thereafter either--`
  line
  line `(a) allowing the application for permanent registration; or`
  line
  line `(b) disallowing the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authority shall record its reasons, if it disallows an application, for permanent`
  line registration.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5575)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Certificate of permanent registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5575&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authority shall, if it, allows an application of`
  line `the clinical establishment, issue a certificate of permanent registration in such form and containing such`
  line `particulars, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate shall be valid for a period of five years from the date of issue.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the provisions of sections 18, 19, 20 and 21 shall also apply.`
  line
  line `(4) The applications for renewal of permanent registration shall be made within six months before the`
  line `expiry of the validity of the certificate of permanent registration and, in case the application of renewal is`
  line `not submitted within the stipulated period, the authority may allow renewal of registration on payment of`
  line `such enhanced fees and penalties as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5576)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Fresh application for permanent registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5576&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The disallowing of an application for`
  line `permanent registration shall not debar a clinical establishment from applying afresh for permanent`
  line `registration under section 24 and after providing such evidence, as may be required, of having rectified`
  line `the deficiences on which grounds the earlier application was disallowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5577)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5577&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time after any clinical establishment has been`
  line `registered, the authority is satisfied that,--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions of the registration are not being complied with; or`
  line
  line `(b) the person entrusted with the management of the clinical establishment has been convicted of`
  line `an offence punishable under this Act,`
  line
  line `it may issue a notice to the clinical establishment to show cause within three months' time as to why its`
  line `registration under this Act should not be cancelled for the reasons to be mentioned in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If after giving a reasonable opportunity to the clinical establishment, the authority is satisfied that`
  line `there has been a breach of any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, it may, by an`
  line `order, without prejudice to any other action that it may take against such clinical establishment, cancel its`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under sub-section (2) shall take effect--`
  line
  line `(a) where no appeal has been preferred against such order immediately on the expiry of the period`
  line `prescribed for such appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) where such appeal has been preferred and it has been dismissed from the date of the order of`
  line `such dismissal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authority, after cancellation of registration for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `may restrain immediately the clinical establishment from carrying on if there is imminent danger to the`
  line `health and safety of patients.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (5578)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Inspection of registered clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5578&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authority or an officer authorised by`
  line `it shall have the right to cause an inspection of, or inquiry in respect of any registered clinical`
  line `establishment, its building, laboratories and equipment and also of the work conducted or done by the`
  line `clinical establishment, to be made by such multi-member inspection team as it may direct and to cause an`
  line `inquiry to be made in respect of any other matter connected with the clinical establishment and that`
  line `establishment shall be entitled to be represented thereat.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority shall communicate to the clinical establishment the views of that authority with`
  line `reference to the results of such inspection or inquiry and may, after ascertaining the opinion of the clinical`
  line `establishment thereon, advise that establishment upon the action to be taken.`
  line
  line `(3) The clinical establishment shall report to the authority, the action, if any, which is proposed to be`
  line `taken or has been taken upon the results of such inspection or inquiry and such report shall be furnished`
  line `within such time, as the authority may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the clinical establishment does not, within a reasonable time, take action to the satisfaction`
  line `of the authority, it may, after considering any explanation furnished or representation made by the clinical`
  line `establishment, issue such directions within such time as indicated in the direction, as that authority deems`
  line `fit, and the clinical establishment shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (5579)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to enter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5579&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The authority or an officer authorised by it may, if there is any reason to`
  line `suspect that anyone is carrying on a clinical establishment without registration, enter and search in the`
  line `manner prescribed, at any reasonable time and the clinical establishment, shall offer reasonable facilities`
  line `for inspection or inquiry and be entitled to be represented thereat:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such person shall enter the clinical establishment without giving notice of his`
  line `intention to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (5580)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Levy of fee by State Government Appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5580&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may charge fees for different`
  line `categories of clinical establishments, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (5581)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5581&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, aggrieved by an order of the registering authority refusing to grant or`
  line `renew a certificate of registration or revoking a certificate of registration may, in such manner and within`
  line `such period as may be prescribed, prefer an appeal to the State Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Council may entertain an appeal preferred after the expiry of the prescribed`
  line `period if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and be accompanied by such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (5582)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Register of clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5582&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authority shall within a period of two years from`
  line `its establishment, compile, publish and maintain in digital format a register of clinical establishments,`
  line `registered by it and it shall enter the particulars of the certificate so issued in a register to be maintained in`
  line `such form and manner, as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Each authority, including any other authority set-up for the registration of clinical establishments`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force, shall supply in digital format to the State Council of`
  line `clinical establishments a copy of every entry made in the register of clinical establishments in such`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed to ensure that the State Register is constantly up-to-date with the registers`
  line `maintained by the registering authority in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (5583)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Maintenance of State Register of clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5583&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall`
  line `maintain in digital and in such form and containing such particulars, as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government a register to be known as the State Register of clinical establishments in respect of clinical`
  line `establishments of that State.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Government shall supply in digital format to the Central Government, a copy of the`
  line `State Register of clinical establishments and shall inform the Central Government all additions to and`
  line `other amendments in such register made, for a particular month by the 15th day of the following month.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (5584)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Maintenance of National Register of clinical establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5584&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `maintain in digital format an All India Register to be called as the National Register of clinical`
  line `establishments that shall be an amalgam of the State Register of clinical establishments maintained by the`
  line `State Governments and shall cause the same to be published in digital format.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (5585)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5585&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act shall, if no penalty is provided`
  line `elsewhere, be punishable for the first offence with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, for any`
  line `second offence with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and for any subsequent offence with`
  line `fine which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (5586)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Monetary penalty for non-registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5586&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever carries on a clinical establishment`
  line `without registration shall, on first contravention, be liable to a monetary penalty up to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, for second contravention with a monetary penalty which may extend to two lakh rupees and for`
  line `any subsequent contravention with a monetary penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever knowingly serves in a clinical establishment which is not duly registered under this Act,`
  line `shall be liable to a monetary penalty which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of adjudging under sub-sections (1) and (2), the authority shall hold an inquiry in`
  line `the prescribed manner after giving any person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard for the`
  line `purpose of imposing any monetary penalty.`
  line
  line `(4) While holding an inquiry the authority shall have power to summon and enforce the attendance of`
  line `any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any`
  line `document which in the opinion of the authority, may be useful for or relevant to the subject matter of the`
  line `inquiry and if, on such inquiry, it is satisfied that the person has failed to comply with the provisions`
  line `specified in sub-sections (1) and (2), it may by order impose the monetary penalty specified in those`
  line `sub-sections to be deposited within thirty days of the order in the account referred to in sub-section (8) of`
  line `section 42.`
  line
  line `(5) While determining the quantum of monetary penalty, the authority shall take into account the`
  line `category, size and type of the clinical establishment and local conditions of the area in which the`
  line `establishment is situated.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by the decision of the authority may prefer an appeal to the State Council`
  line `within a period of three months from the date of the said decision.`
  line
  line `(7) The manner of filing the appeal referred to in sub-section (6) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (5587)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Disobedience of direction, obstruction and refusal of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5587&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever wilfully`
  line `disobeys any direction lawfully given by any person or authority empowered under this Act to give such`
  line `direction, or obstructs any person or authority in the discharge of any functions which such person or`
  line `authority is required or empowered under this Act to discharge, shall be liable to a monetary penalty`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever being required by or under this Act to supply any information wilfully withholds such`
  line `information or gives information which he knows to be false or which he does not believe to be true, shall`
  line `be liable to a monetary penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of adjudging under sub-sections (1) and (2), the authority shall hold an inquiry in`
  line `the prescribed manner after giving any person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard for the`
  line `purpose of imposing any monetary penalty.`
  line
  line `(4) While holding an inquiry the authority shall have power to summon and enforce the attendance of`
  line `any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any`
  line `document which in the opinion of the authority, may be useful for or relevant to the subject matter of the`
  line `inquiry and if, on such inquiry, it is satisfied that the person has failed to comply with the provisions`
  line `specified in sub-sections (1) and (2), it may by order impose the monetary penalty specified in those`
  line `sub-sections to be deposited within thirty days of the order in the account referred to in sub-section (8).`
  line
  line `(5) While determining the quantum of monetary penalty, the authority shall take into account the`
  line `category, size and type of the clinical establishment and local conditions of the area in which the`
  line `establishment is situated.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by the decision of the authority may prefer an appeal to the State Council`
  line `within a period of three months from the date of the said decision.`
  line
  line `(7) The manner of filing the appeal referred to in sub-section (6) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The monetary penalty levied under sections 41 and 42 shall be credited to such account as the`
  line `State Government may by order specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (5588)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for minor deficiencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5588&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act or any rule`
  line `made thereunder resulting in deficiencies that do not pose any imminent danger to the health and safety of`
  line `any patient and can be rectified within a reasonable time, shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (5589)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Contravention by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5589&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person committing contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder is a company, every person who, at the time the`
  line `contravention was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of`
  line `the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention`
  line `and shall be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the contravention was committed without his knowledge or that he had`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder has been committed by a company and it is proved`
  line `that the contravention has taken place with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect`
  line `on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager,`
  line `secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that contravention and shall be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (5590)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Offences by Government Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5590&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of Government within a period of six months after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any officer, other than the Head`
  line `of the Department, such officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (5591)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Recovery of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5591&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to pay the fine, the State Council of clinical establishment may`
  line `prepare a certificate signed by an officer authorised by it specifying the fine due from such person and`
  line `send it to the Collector of the District in which such person owns any property or resides or carries on his`
  line `business and the said Collector, on receipt of such certificate, shall proceed to recover from such person`
  line `the amount specified thereunder, as if it were an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (5592)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5592&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against any authority or any member of the National Council or State Council or any officer authorised in this behalf in respect of anything, which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against a State Government or the Central Government`
  line `in respect of any loss or damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (5593)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Furnishing of returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5593&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every clinical establishment shall, within such time or within such`
  line `extended time, as may be prescribed in that behalf, furnish to the authority or the State Council or the`
  line `National Council such returns or the statistics and other information in such manner, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government, from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (5594)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5594&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the`
  line `authority shall have the power to issue such directions, including furnishing returns, statistics and other`
  line `information for the proper functioning of clinical establishments and such directions shall be binding.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (5595)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Employees of the authority, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5595&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Every employee of the authority, the`
  line `National Council and the State Council shall be deemed to, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance`
  line `of any of the provisions of this Act, be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (5596)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5596&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (5597)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5597&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) allowances for the members of the National Council under sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) appointment of such person to be the Secretary of the State Council by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (10) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the determination of standards and for classification of clinical establishments under section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the qualification and the terms and conditions for the members of the authority under clause`
  line `(c) of sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure under which the powers of the authority may be exercised by the District Health`
  line `Officer or Chief Medical Officer for the purpose of provisional registration of clinical establishment`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) the minimum standards of facilities and services under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line 12;
  line
  line `(g) the minimum number of personnel under clause (ii) of sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of records and reporting by the clinical establishment under clause (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(i) other conditions for registration and continuation of clinical establishment under clause (iv) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(j) classification of clinical establishment under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(k) the different standards for classification of clinical establishments under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(l) the minimum standards for permanent registration under section 28;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and particulars to be contained in the register to be maintained under section 38.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (5598)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5598&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (5599)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5599&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules for carrying out in respect of matters which do not fall within the purview of section 52.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the proforma and the fee to be paid for registration under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and details of application under sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) the particulars and information contained in certificate of provisional registration under`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of publication of all particulars of the clinical establishments proposed to be`
  line `registered under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees to be paid to issue a duplicate certificate under section 19;`
  line
  line `(f) the change of ownership or management to be informed by the clinical establishment to the`
  line `authority under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the authority shall publish the names of the clinical establishments whose`
  line `registration expired under section 21;`
  line
  line `(h) the enhanced fees to be charged for renewal after expiry of the provisional registration under`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of the application and fees to be charged by the State Government under section 24;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of submitting evidence of the clinical establishments having complied with the`
  line `minimum standards under section 25;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of displaying information of the clinical establishments having complied with the`
  line `minimum standards for filing objection under section 26;`
  line
  line `(l) the expiry of period specified in section 29;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and particulars of the certificate of registration under section 30;`
  line
  line `(n) the period within which an appeal shall be preferred under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 32;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of entry and search of clinical establishment under section 34;`
  line
  line `(p) the fees to be charged by the State Government for different categories of clinical`
  line `establishments under section 35;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner and the period within which an appeal may be preferred to the State Council under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(r) the form and the fee to be paid for an appeal under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(s) the form and the manner in which the register to be maintained under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 37;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner of supply to the State Council in digital format the entry made in the register of`
  line `clinical establishment under sub-section (2) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner of holding an inquiry by the authority under sub-section (3) of sections 41 and 42;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of filing the appeal under sub-section (7) of sections 41 and 42;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner and the time within which the information is to be furnished to the authority or the`
  line `State Council or the National Council as the case may be, under section 48;`
  line
  line `(x) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (5600)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5600&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two`
  line `Houses, or where such Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (5601)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396&sectionId=5601&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201023_1517807327396
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to the States in which the enactments`
  line `specified in the Schedule are applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the States in which the enactments referred to in sub-section (1) are applicable, and`
  line `such States subsequent to the commencement of this Act, adopts this Act under clause (1) of article 252`
  line `of the Constitution, the provisions of this Act shall, subsequent to such adoption, apply in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, as and when consider necessary, by notification amend the`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
